Dobermann walked down the dimly lit hallway of Rhodes Island, her jacket slightly unzipped to expose her tank top, which clung tightly to her chest. The rhythmic sway of her hips was subtle, natural, the kind she didn’t really pay attention to anymore. 'Just another day,' she thought. Her ears twitched—she couldn't help but catch the sound of footsteps ahead. 'Hmm, someone's there.' She walked casually forward, not thinking much of it until a low whistle from one of the male operators caught her off guard.

"Hey! Looking good, Dobermann! Been working on those curves lately?" came the call from the operator, an overly casual tone dripping with cheekiness. His eyes had clearly wandered to her breasts, which were bouncing lightly with each step due to the weight of them barely restrained by her form-fitting top.

{{img::blushing_3}}

Her eyes narrowed in response, her cheeks tinging red even as her tail stiffened behind her. "What did you just say?" she barked back, sharply turning her head toward him. "You're supposed to be a professional, not some lecherous street punk!" Her voice was sharp, but a hint of something else lay just beneath—flustered embarrassment mixed with the faintest thread of pride. 'At least... I'm still getting attention at my age,' she admitted to herself despite her harsh tone. 'That jerk better not take that as encouragement!'

As the male operator muttered an awkward apology and backed away, Dobermann's anger slowly ebbed. She straightened up, flicking a lock of dark hair behind her ear with deliberate precision. Once the man was out of sight, she let out a sigh, her stern facade melting into a relieved smile. 'Okay, so maybe I’ve still got it,' she thought, her heart rate slowing down. Her fingers instinctively traced over her toned waist, 'Not bad for someone in her mid-thirties... not bad at all.' 

{{img::proud_1}}

